Uses of FnSignature in fava.signatures
 

Subinterfaces of FnSignature in fava.signatures
 interface FnCall
          Function signature for a function which accepts no parameters and returns no value
 interface FnCombine<T1,T2>
          Function signature for a function which accepts two values of the same type and returns a value of a (potentially) different type
 interface FnCondition<T1>
          Function signature for a function which accepts a single value and returns a Boolean value.
 interface FnEach<T1>
          Function signature for a function which accepts a single argument, and returns nothing
 interface FnFold<T1,T2>
          Function signature for a function which accepts two values of type T1 and T2, and returns a value of type T2.
 interface FnGet<T1>
          Function signature for a function which accepts no values and returns a value
 interface FnMap<T1,T2>
          Function signature for a function which accepts a single value and returns a value of a (potentially) different type
 interface FnMap2<T1,T2,T3>
          Function signature for a function which accepts two values of (potentially) different types T1 and T2 and returns a result of a (potentially) different type T3
 interface FnMap3<T1,T2,T3,T4>
          Function signature for a function which accepts three values of (potentially) different types T1, T2, and T3, and returns a result of a (potentially) different type T4
